===References===
*[[Strong's concordance]] number:  [http://www.biblestudytools.net/Lexicons/Greek/grk.cgi?number=4863&version=kjv G4863] 

===Pronunciation===
*συνάγω / sunagō / soon-ag'-o
=== Etymology ===

*From [[σύν]] {{GG|4862}} and [[ἄγω]] {{GG|71}}; to lead together, that is, collect or convene; specifically to entertain (hospitably): 
=== Verb ===
+ [[accompany]], [[assemble]] (selves, together), bestow, come together, [[gather]] (selves together, up, together), lead into, resort, take in.